## Key Takeaways for Families

**Start here:** Call 1-800-282-8096 to reach your local Aging and People with Disabilities office. They can determine which tier your loved one qualifies for and walk through the application process.[3]

**Income matters most:** Oregon's approach to income calculation is generous—they start with gross income, subtract $20, and apply additional deductions for earned income.[8] Families should apply even if income appears to exceed the stated limits.

**No asset limits:** Unlike many states, Oregon doesn't count savings or resources, making it easier for families with modest savings to qualify.[3][8]

**QI program caveat:** If your loved one qualifies for any other Oregon Medicaid benefit, they cannot use the QI/SMF program.[3] Additionally, this program has annual enrollment caps and may close to new applicants.[3]

**Annual updates:** Income limits increase each March, so families should verify eligibility yearly.[3]

